observations.recommendation:
We recommended, and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive: 

(3) a. Require the Inventory Committee and Property Custodian to:

Formulate plans and strategize the complete conduct of physical count of all its PPE, and prepare and submit the RPCPPE not later than January 31 of the ensuing year in compliance with Section 124 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGUs, Volume I; 

Reconcile their RPCPPE with the records of the Municipal Accountant; and

Ensure the report’s usability by including all the required information in the RPCPPE, as illustrated in the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume II;

(4) b. Require the Municipal Accountant to:

 Provide depreciation for depreciable PPEs with an aggregate carrying amount of ₱31,028,905.38 in accordance with Paragraphs 43 and 71 of IPSAS 17;

Provide the correct residual value of depreciable PPEs and compute the monthly depreciation expense in accordance with COA issued accounting policies and prepare the necessary adjusting entry to reflect the correct balance of each PPE accounts; and

(5) c. Create an Inventory Committee to complete the physical inventory in three (3) months or less, and to prepare and submit the approved Physical Inventory Plan to the COA Audit Team at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled start of inventory-taking activities; and ensure full implementation of “One-time cleansing of PPE accounts” as provided under COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 1, 2020.

We recommended, and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive direct the:

(17) a. BAC Chairperson to submit the contract within five (5) working days from the time the contract is perfected;

(18) b. Municipal Engineer to:

Immediately submit justification on the unimplemented and delayed projects;

Monitor and reconcile with the Budget Office the actual accomplishment of every project.;

(19) c. BAC and the Municipal Engineer to expedite the procurement and implementation process to ensure timely realization of the planned projects; and

(20) d. Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Engineer to stop charging ineligible expenses to the 20% development fund.

(33) We recommended and the management agreed that the Local Chief Executive: 

a. Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare Journal Entry Voucher to adjust the properties below the capitalization threshold and ensure that all future acquisitions of properties below the capitalization threshold of ₱50,000.00 be recorded in accordance with COA Circular No. 2022-004; 

(34) b. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to take up necessary adjusting entries to revert over-depreciation of various Equipment and to recognize depreciation of Other Land Improvement Account by corresponding prior years’ adjustment in the books to be closed to the Government Equity Account, 

(35) c. Require the Municipal Accountant to disclose in the notes to FS the useful lives of each category of recognized PPE;

(7) d. Require the Municipal Accountant and the Property & Supply Officer to prepare and maintain the PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards, respectively, in order to facilitate the periodic reconciliation if the PPE accounts with results of the physical inventory taking.

We recommended and management agreed that the LCE:

a. Direct the Municipal Assessor to provide the Assessment Roll to the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer; 

