observations.managementAction:
a) Strictly abide with the provisions of DILG Memorandum Circular No. 2012-73 and refrain from charging expenses not related to disaster risk reduction management activities.
b) Refrain from charging expenses against QRF without resolution and declaration of state of calamity.
c) Instruct the Municipal Budget Officer to include the administrative expenses of the LDRRMO in the regular budget and prepare a separate budget for the 5% LDRRMF in accordance with Section 5.1.1 of COA Circular 2012-002;
d) Require the PPAs for the LDRRMF to include in the LDRRMFIP the projects and activities to be funded out of unexpended balances of the LDRRMF of the previous year;
e) Require the Municipal Budget Officer to maintain separate registries for the LDRRMF-MOOE and Capital Outlay for the current year and for the continuing appropriations of the previous years;
f) Require the Municipal Accountant to determine the unexpended balances of MOOE 70% as well as the 30% QRF for CYs 2014 to 2017 and facilitate the transfer of the balances to the special trust fund.
